<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" TextAlignment="Justify"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
 
<Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
This category contains samples demonstrating various editing capabilities of Essential PDF.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Here is a list of samples with descriptions.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Merge Documents</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to merge multiple PDF documents using Essential PDF.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Named Bookmark</Bold> - This sample demonstrates Essential PDF's support for bookmark with named destination in PDF documents.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Split Document</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to split an existing PDF document into multiple PDF documents.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Import and Stamp</Bold> - This sample demonstrates Essential PDF's support for importing a page from an existing PDF and stamping the PDF file.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Overlay Documents</Bold> - This sample demonstrates Essential PDF's support for importing PDF documents as templates.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Booklet</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how to create a booklet from an existing PDF document.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>